st reflexes, they are in many cases, simply a blur. A great diffinition of a true wizard would be a combination of fast reflexes (physical), wisdom (mental), and possibly an attitude of absolute cool under fire. In RL you can be as immature or mature as you want to be. In EQOA though, you can rise above your RL personality and RP into a respectable wizard.<br>
<br>
 The following is a few examples of immaturity:<br>
1. Ninja looting.<br>
2. Kill stealing.<br>
3. Training a group.<br>
4. Asking strangers for loot, rez, sow, and invis. All with out saying at least hello first.<br>
5. Killing greens on the way to a raid while in a group.<br>
 (the list can go on and on, but this isn't my point)<br>
<br>
The following is a short list of things to gain the respect of your group and or your guild:<br>
<br>
1.Explore first. Pick an area that is for your level or even higher and travel it in all directions to see what is available to your hunting group. Its best to know it inside and out.<br>
<br>
2.Protect your group mates when ever possible. If someone leaves for a break, then invis his toon, stay close by and notify the others in the group that you are in a protective stance.<br>
<br>
3.If you are leading a group to an area and you hear the sounds of an attack, stop, turn around and go back to see if it is one of your group under attack.<br>
<br>
4.Never nuke until at least one red bubble is gone on the mob your group is attacking. (there are some exceptions on light blue's)<br>
<br>
5.Even after the mana/regen to nuke changes, you still should use one combination of two light nukes (100-120 DD) for long expeditions. Also piggyback a heavy duty nuke for emergency use. (180-250 DD).<br>
<br>
6.Use 2 medium duty nukes for quest kills or quickies to help others (120 - 180 DD).<br>
<br>
7.Even if you are not a leader of the group you can still maintain a steady control with your wizard's abilities. Use arcane science (rooting) on the rear adds first.<br>
<br>
8.Tell your group to keep backing up and keep the roots coming. They should see the green shower come down on the mob and know that you are rooting. Best to tell them how you use arcane science way a head of time. Also what to expect on a train or respawn adds, etc.<br>
 <br>
9.When you run out of mana, don't keep hitting the nuke fire button endlessly. Watch for the hilite to change on that nuke symbol before firing. Why? Because its very annoying to others in your group to hear the constant nuking sound. On a theater surround sound it sounds like all hell broke loose when actually you are tapped out of mana and are powerless.<br>
<br>
10.Killing the stable boy will cost you! We all see the new adventurers do it, but if they scroll up on the chat screen they will find that they just went negative in faction somewhere in Tunaria. The day will come that they can't get a certain coach will be from killing the stable boy, etc.<br>
<br>
 There are hundreds of ways to make yourself worth more to others, but the important thing here is respect. You picked a wizard for your toon, but with it comes a respect from other classes for your ability to do heavy direct damage to mobs. To achieve that 'ice water for blood in your veins' attitude that is admired by most is only achieved by caring for your group and your guild.<br>
<br>
Several of the wizards on this board I have tons of mad respect for. Thats because they don't act like a showoff, or try to act like they are the king of nukes, etc. They gain that respect out of knowledge, tactics, strategy, patience, perserverence, and a caring attitude. The young ones have the advantage of reflexes. They have the opportunity to become sought after for their abilities and coolness of attitude. <br>
<br>
Now this was a true rant and rave...lol..!!<br>
